    <Folder>
      <name>Intelligence Summary</name>
      <Placemark>
        <name>AI Council Assessment</name>
        <styleUrl>#intel</styleUrl>
        <description>The U.S. military is demonstrating a globally distributed posture of persistent presence and deterrence, with particular emphasis on the Indo-Pacific and European theaters. Carrier strike groups (CSGs) and amphibious ready groups (ARGs) are strategically deployed across critical maritime chokepoints, including the South China Sea, East China Sea, Arabian Sea, and Mediterranean Sea. This deployment pattern reflects a deliberate strategy to counter regional threats, maintain freedom of navigation, and reassure allies amid growing Chinese assertiveness and Russian aggression. The Western Pacific sees the highest concentration of U.S. naval power, with multiple CSGs operating near the Korean Peninsula and South China Sea, indicating heightened readiness in response to North Korean provocations and Chinese maritime expansion. Mediterranean deployments, including USS Dwight D. Eisenhower and USS Harry S. Truman, underscore NATO commitments and the need to counter Russian and Iranian influence in the region. Amphibious ready groups are actively conducting exercises with regional partners, enhancing interoperability and rapid response capabilities. In the Western Hemisphere, U.S. forces are engaged in counter-narcotics operations in the Eastern Pacific, with recent strikes on suspected drug boats highlighting the ongoing commitment to disrupt illicit trafficking networks. The integration of space-based tracking capabilities, as evidenced by the SpaceX $4.16B contract for space-based air movement-target indicators, further enhances the U.S. military&#39;s ability to monitor and respond to dynamic threats across multiple domains. The overall assessment indicates a military posture designed to deter aggression, maintain global maritime security, and support allied security interests while addressing emerging challenges from near-peer competitors.</description>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>0,0,0</coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
    </Folder>
